   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kids: Plant Trees, Plant Water, Protect Life!</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">October 2018. The IPCC Report tells us we&apos;re heading for a temperature rise of 1.5 Celsius by 2030. Maybe sooner. Climate change: floods, fires, hurricanes, droughts - Bad News! This is about us, people. If we don&apos;t do something fast, we&apos;ll all be on the endangered species list. Good News: we know that trees = water, and water = life. So we&apos;re harnessing the energy of kids and youth to spread the word, roll up their sleeves and plant 5,000 trees to capture carbon, protect water and plant life.</narrative>
  </description>
